Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C. Peel and grate the @beetroot{1}(peeled and grated). Pick the @mint{1}(leaves picked from their stalks and finely chopped) and discard the stalks. Remove the root from the @spring onion{3}(root removed and finely sliced) and finely slice. Drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1}(drained and rinsed) in a #colander{} under cold running water.

Put the kidney beans in a #mixing bowl{} and break them up with a #potato masher{} (a few left whole is fine). Add the @ground coriander{1.5}, spring onion, grated beetroot and half the mint. Crumble in the @feta cheese{1}, add the @gram flour{2} and combine evenly.

Shape the mixture into balls, six per person, then squish each one to flatten it slightly. Line a #baking tray{} with some #baking paper{} and lay the falafel out in a single layer. Bake on the top shelf of your oven for ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, make the tzatziki! Cut the @cucumber{1/2}(cut in half lengthways and seeds scraped out) and scrape out the seeds with a #spoon{} (discard the seeds). Chop into 1cm cubes. Pop in a #small bowl{} and add the remaining mint and the @Greek style natural yoghurt{1}. Season with a small pinch of @salt{pinch} and a grind of @black pepper{grind} and mix together.

Roughly chop the @black olives{30} and put them in a #large bowl{} with the @baby watercress{1}. Drizzle over the @olive oil{1} and toss together.

Pop a #frying pan{} on medium heat (no oil). Once hot, lay in a @super soft tortilla with whole wheat{4}. Fry until lightly toasted, ~{1-2%mins} each side. Remove to a #plate{} and cover with #foil{} to keep warm. Repeat with the other tortillas until you have two each. Take everything to the table so people can build their own wraps. We like to lay out a tortilla, add some salad, pop three falafel on top and finish with tzatziki before rolling up and tucking in. Enjoy!